  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Criminal law is the body of rules that defines conduct the state prohibits and authorizes punishment for violations. Unlike [civil law](./civil-law.md), where one party sues another for compensation, criminal law is prosecuted by the state on behalf of the public. The defendant faces not a private plaintiff but the government, with its full investigative and coercive apparatus.",
